<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="communication-n">communication <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kəˌmjuːnɪ'keɪʃn/    美 /kəˌmjuːnɪ'keɪʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 交流；沟通：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Good <strong>communication skills</strong> include learning body language. 
良好的沟通技巧包括学会使用身势语。</p><footer>人教④ – 4</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The telephone is a <strong>means of communication</strong>. 
电话是一种通讯方式。</p><footer>北师大⑧ – 22</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>通讯系统；交通 (网)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>communication system / links / techonology</strong>
通讯系统/网/技术</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Big cities usually have excellent rail and road communications. 
大城市通常有完备的铁路和公路交通网。</p></div></div>